parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Cable Failure and Electrical Short
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery cables can cause an electrical short, leading to engine fires, vehicle stalling, and accidents, which can result in injuries, property damage, and even total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the hood area
erratic lighting operation
engine stalling without warning
vehicle unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues with Battery Cable Insulation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall on the insulation of the battery cables was not done due to dealer location problems, which can lead to a short circuit, causing engine fires and accidents.
symptoms: None reported
as this issue is related to the recall process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling without warning can cause accidents, especially at high speeds, which can result in injuries and property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling without warning
loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause serious injuries, including facial trauma, eye damage, and chemical burns, and can lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
often when turning the ignition key or at low speeds
without any impact or collision. The deployment can cause physical harm
including bloody nose and eye
chemical burns
and swelling of the face.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries and accidents, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, leaving occupants unprotected.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the supplemental restraining system light comes on
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to engine damage and fires.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates erratically
the vehicle smokes after sudden acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unattended vehicle fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially harm people in the vicinity. The root cause of these fires is unknown, but it may be related to an electrical or mechanical fault.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while parked and unattended
with no apparent warning signs or symptoms.
